		<text id="swap_text01" x="584" y="112" width="189" height="" autosize="H" style="REFERENCE" visible="false" fx="INTRO_SHOW" hidefx="INTRO_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;Right. Parents need to know that what they do is important, and that children's brains are malleable. &lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;Even if parents feel they have made mistakes during the first few years of their child's life, reassure parents that they can still greatly influence their child and shape his or her development. It's never too late.&lt;/P&gt;</content>
		</text>
		<text id="swap_text02" x="" y="" width="187" height="" autosize="H" style="REFERENCE" visible="false" fx="INTRO_SHOW" hidefx="INTRO_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;That's right. Help parents understand that each child will develop on his or her own unique timeline. &lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;At the same time, if the child is missing several milestones or if the parent has additional questions or concerns, the child may need to be referred to a medical provider for further evaluation.&lt;/P&gt;</content>
		</text>
		<text id="swap_text03" x="" y="" width="195" height="" autosize="H" style="REFERENCE" visible="false" fx="INTRO_SHOW" hidefx="INTRO_HIDE">
